Liszt the man in all his many shades and personal reinventions: child prodigy, Romantic eccentric, fervent Catholic, actor, lothario, celebrity, businessman, genius, and extravagant show-off. The author immerses the reader in the intrigues of the nineteenth-century European glitterati (including Liszt’s powerful patrons, the monstrous Wagner clan) while exploring the true, complex face of the artist and the soul of his music. No other Liszt biography in English is as colorful, witty, and compulsively readable, or reveals as much about the true nature of this extraordinary, outrageous talent.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aComposersvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Composers & Musicians.2bisacsh1 aHilmes, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpencer, Stewart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030018293440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021946340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300219463423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300219463/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY